article.description: Francisco Condado kicked a 28-yard field goal with 2:46 to play to help Nicholls State slip past Lamar 30-28 Saturday night.
article.headline: Condado's late FG lifts Nicholls State over Lamar, 30-28
article.linkText: Condado's late FG lifts Nicholls State over Lamar, 30-28
article.story: BEAUMONT, Texas -- Francisco Condado kicked a 28-yard field goal with 2:46 to play to help Nicholls State slip past Lamar 30-28 Saturday night. Lamar (4-5, 3-4 Southland Conference) didn't trail until Condado's kick, which was set up by Sean Eppinette's fumble recovery at the Colonels' 33 with 10:01 left. Condado missed an extra point following a 5-yard touchdown run by Landry Klann with 5:08 remaining in the third, leaving Nicholls behind 28-27. The Cardinals used a 13-play, 74-yard drive on their last possession to set up a short field attempt, but missed a 23-yarder as time expired. Nicholls (2-7, 2-5), which came into the game averaging 162.2 yards rushing, finished with 415. Tobias Lofton set career highs with 17 carries and 154 yards -- including an 82-yard touchdown run -- and Michael Henry added 100 yards and two touchdowns. Lamar's Kade Harrington finished with 255 yards rushing, giving him 1,805 this season, breaking the Southland Conference single-season record with two games to play.
